Program: Outlook
Title: Raped for Being a Lesbian in South African
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p03kbsj6
Last Broadcast Date: Not available
As every 29 seconds a woman is raped in South Africa, a lesbian talks about being subjected to a 'corrective rape' in 1991. The Rose has Thorns campaign is aiming to raise awareness of homophobia in South Africa. Also: French climber Alain Robert is known as 'Spiderman'. His next venture is to climb the Europa Tower, the tallest skyscraper in the Baltic states. Why Rwanda has banned motorcycle taxis. Show less